line_2: He seems a dauncing as he walks,

line_1: With her of Tarsels, and of Lures he talks.
line_2: A Falc'ner Henry is, when Emma Hawks:

line_1: No more in ponds the gosling talks,
line_2: But sails secure on gravel walks.

line_1: Each fool of Delia's figure talks,
line_2: But, for my part, whene'er she walks,

line_1: Tho' all a syren as she talks,
line_2: And all a goddess as she walks,

line_1: Here sighs a Jar, and there a Goose-pye talks;
line_2: A Pipkin there like Homer's Tripod walks;
